{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51993e7f-cf38-4877-a5a6-89b1a438ebb4","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated  += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created` → `Activated` |\n| Switch away | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` |\n| Switch back | `Resumed` → `Activated` |\n| Close / kill | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` → `Destroying` |\n\n> `Backgrounding` is iOS/Mac Catalyst-specific and fires when the app enters the background (use it to save state).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6a2d1b04-3162-49b8-a73f-848e87f45dcf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for debugging/logging purposes. This is a general knowledge question that I can answer directly without needing to explore any codebase.","outputTokens":409,"requestId":"77EA:1E7A6A:82EE9E5:9110F15:69EABE39"},"id":"85b07993-c248-451d-a860-3d8dfbbbb679","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:50:11.362Z","parentId":"a7f8bc8f-5bbb-4fe8-8be8-cc23de3ba522"}
